rComments: Worst prof at UofT. She was so mean that she would literally insult you in the face. The course is hard and difficult as hell. If it weren't becoz of my curriculum requirements, I wouldn't take it.

Talks about random examples in class rather than providing clear explanations of th essentials. Assignments are hard for the sake of being hard. Nothing instructive about them. Marking is done with obsession to small technical details. Just horrible.

She taught the material very concisely and organized. She helped when you ask proper questions, though she likes you to learn this stuff on your own. Seeing that it was a *hard* thinking course, she taught how to think and not depend on others. One of my top 5 profs in Computer Science and I haven't taken her course since first year.

Previous comments don't begin to describe the disaster. 65% of the class dropped and she failed 40% of the rest. This gives her as a prof. success rate 60%, or failed. The stats should give you an idea of the obvious inability to communicate material across, address problems or pace requirements.
THe worst teacher I have ever had in my life.

Half of the class dropped, still end up with a d+ average. But you will learn how to teach yourself by taking her course.

Stay away! The first assignment was fine, the next for BRUTAL! Average on the midterm 33%!  With a 50% drop rate after the test. Assignments seem like they come from a grad course. The we do easy stuff in lectures but come midterm and assignments you wonder what happened to the lecture material.

lectures do not reflect assignments at all, and both lectures and assignments only slightly reflect the test, so almost all the material that's marked is self-study. she's not really available to ask questions and there's no course newsgroup so if the handout is unclear you're on your own. (contd)

This is just one of "I'm smarter then you" profs, whose only goal in life is to screw as many people as possible over. Tests are HELL compared to previous course offerings, her lecturing is useless and unclear, she's not enthusiastic, and on top of everything,she yells at you if you ask a question.

Man, and to think i have taken her twice! Unless you already know the course do not take her. She is bad at explaining. Maybe not so bad - just whatever her lectures are - completely different from the assignments(which are WAY harder-enriched courseOrNo
